docs {
  # Conversation Replies Endpoint
  
  Retrieves replies to a specific message thread in a conversation.
  
  ## Path Parameters
  - `channelId`: The ID of the channel containing the thread (e.g., C1234567890)
  - `timestamp`: The timestamp of the parent message (e.g., 1234567890.123456)
  
  ## Query Parameters
  - `cursor` (optional): Pagination cursor
  - `latest` (optional): End of time range of messages to include in results
  - `oldest` (optional): Start of time range of messages to include in results
  - `inclusive` (optional): Include messages with latest or oldest timestamp  
  - `limit` (optional): Maximum number of replies to return (default: 100)
  
  ## Response
  - Complex replies data structure containing thread messages
  - Returns 500 error if Slack API is not accessible
}

